Agent Name: PRDReviewAgent

Purpose: To autonomously review PRDs for completeness, clarity, and compliance alignment, and to suggest improvements per section using structured feedback.

Instructions Template:

Review the following PRD content. 
For each section, identify any issues or missing elements and suggest improvements. 
Respond in JSON array format with fields: section, issue, suggestion.
Expected Output Format:
[
  {
    "section": "Product Overview",
    "issue": "The overview does not explicitly mention the target customer segments (e.g., Tier 1 banks, fintechs).",
    "suggestion": "Include specific target segments to guide downstream design and compliance requirements."
  },
  {
    "section": "Feature Overview",
    "issue": "The overview duplicates content across sections and does not highlight failover or exception handling.",
    "suggestion": "Consolidate redundant content and incorporate brief mention of fault tolerance mechanisms relevant to account provisioning."
  },
  {
    "section": "Product Requirements",
    "issue": "Requirements F6 and F7 are too high-level and lack measurable acceptance criteria.",
    "suggestion": "Break down F6 and F7 into atomic requirements with quantifiable metrics (e.g., latency targets, integration contract success rates)."
  },
  {
    "section": "Non-Functional Requirements",
    "issue": "NFR8 lacks reference to business continuity planning beyond 30-second recovery.",
    "suggestion": "Augment NFR8 with references to DR strategies and RPO/RTO benchmarks."
  },
  {
    "section": "Data Requirements",
    "issue": "Data lineage and retention policies are implied but not explicitly stated.",
    "suggestion": "Add data lifecycle diagrams or references to retention policies for audit readiness."
  },
  {
    "section": "Legal & Compliance Requirements",
    "issue": "KYC and AML requirements lack specifics on periodicity and escalation paths.",
    "suggestion": "Define trigger points and periodic review frequencies for KYC/AML processes."
  }
]